# AI Designer Preferences + API Keys Management

Persist AI Designer settings (selected provider, model, base URL) and API Keys **per provider** to the database. Add a "Manage API Keys" panel in Settings > Preferences.

## Proposed Changes

---

### BFF — Database Schema ([schema.prisma](file:///c:/Users/ianache/Desktop/DATA/01-DOCUMENTOS/02-PROYECTOS/103-APIManager/apps/bff/prisma/schema.prisma))
#### [MODIFY] [schema.prisma](file:///c:/Users/ianache/Desktop/DATA/01-DOCUMENTOS/02-PROYECTOS/103-APIManager/apps/bff/prisma/schema.prisma)
- Add `UserLLMApiKey` model: stores `userId`, `providerId`, `apiKey` (encrypted or plain-text), timestamps. Uses `@@unique([userId, providerId])`.
- Add `UserPreferences` model: stores `userId`, `preferredProvider`, `preferredModel`, `customApiUrl`, timestamps. `@id` is `userId`.

---

### BFF — New Routes (`src/routes/userPreferences.ts`)
#### [NEW] [userPreferences.ts](file:///c:/Users/ianache/Desktop/DATA/01-DOCUMENTOS/02-PROYECTOS/103-APIManager/apps/bff/src/routes/userPreferences.ts)

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `GET` | `/user-preferences` | Returns current user's `UserPreferences` + all their `UserLLMApiKey` records |
| `PUT` | `/user-preferences` | Upserts `UserPreferences` (provider, model, apiUrl) for the current user |
| `PUT` | `/user-api-keys/:providerId` | Upserts a single API Key for the current user + given provider |
| `DELETE` | `/user-api-keys/:providerId` | Deletes a specific API Key for user+provider |

All routes require a valid JWT (`request.user`).  

